The Telegraph - Calcutta
 India clubbed with Australia, Holland
New Delhi: India will have their task cut out in the pool stage of the Olympic hockey event after being grouped with defending champions The Netherlands and strong contenders Australia. According to the draw released by the IHF in Brussels on Wednesday, Asia Cup champions India have been placed in pool B along with Australia, Argentina, The Netherlands, New Zealand and South Africa. South Africas participation in the Games, however, will depend on a Court of Arbitration of Sports (CAS) ruling on whether hosts Greece should be given automatic entry to the Athens Games. Asian Games gold-medallists South Korea and Pakistan have been clubbed in pool A along with world champions Germany, Spain, Britain and Egypt. India finished fourth behind The Netherlands, Spain and Pakistan in last months Olympic qualifiers in Madrid. ATHENS GROUPINGSPool A: Egypt, Germany, Britain, Korea, Pakistan, Spain. Pool B: India, Argentina, Australia, The Netherlands, New Zealand, South Africa. (Reuters)  Copyright 
